{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ideal size","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of its children both dimensions:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can think of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the creation of a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view, and the specific effects of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" depends on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"particular view and how you have configured it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertical dimensions, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixes this view at its ideal size."}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"title":"fixedSize